#!/bin/sh
# Kotlin dawn CLI launcher — the golden-diff reference while the transition
# runs (M8 phase 3). bin/dawn is the selfhost toolchain now; this stays the
# oracle side of scripts/selfhost-*-diff.sh until phase 5 archives Kotlin.
set -e

# resolve symlinks (e.g. ~/.local/bin/dawn) so ROOT is the real repo checkout
SELF="$(readlink -f "$0")"
ROOT="$(cd "$(dirname "$SELF")/.." && pwd)"
JAR="$ROOT/compiler/build/libs/dawn.jar"

if [ ! -f "$JAR" ]; then
  echo "error: $JAR not found" >&2
  echo "build it first: cd $ROOT && gradle :compiler:fatJar" >&2
  exit 2
fi

# if JAVA_HOME is unset, try GraalVM under ~/tools. Both layouts: macOS bundles
# the JDK under Contents/Home, Linux tarballs put bin/ at the top level.
if [ -z "$JAVA_HOME" ]; then
  for d in "$HOME"/tools/graalvm-*/Contents/Home "$HOME"/tools/graalvm-*; do
    if [ -x "$d/bin/java" ]; then
      JAVA_HOME="$d"
      export JAVA_HOME
      break
    fi
  done
fi

if [ -n "$JAVA_HOME" ] && [ -x "$JAVA_HOME/bin/java" ]; then
  exec "$JAVA_HOME/bin/java" -jar "$JAR" "$@"
fi
exec java -jar "$JAR" "$@"
